.START 

Giant Resources Ltd., an Australian mining company, said it is holding preliminary discussions with a syndicate of investors concerning a possible sale of Giant's Canadian mining assets. 

The company said these assets could include its 43.7% interest in lead-zinc producer Curragh Resources Inc., and its controlling interest in the gold-mining operations within Pamour Group, including Pamour Inc., Giant Yellowknife Mines Ltd., ERG Resources Inc., and Pamorex Minerals Inc. 

"The syndicate has been represented in these discussions by Curragh Resources Inc. of Toronto.
No agreements have been concluded and discussions are continuing," Giant Resources said in a statement.
It didn't elaborate.
Giant Resources is 42.2% owned by Pioneer International Ltd., an Australian building-materials, oil and mining concern. 

